40: /**
41:  * This class manages the fetching process with the brokers.
42:  * <p>
43:  * Thread-safety:
44:  * Requests and responses of Fetcher may be processed by different threads since heartbeat
45:  * thread may process responses. Other operations are single-threaded and invoked only from
46:  * the thread polling the consumer.
47:  * <ul>
48:  *     <li>If a response handler accesses any shared state of the Fetcher (e.g. FetchSessionHandler),
49:  *     all access to that state must be synchronized on the Fetcher instance.</li>
50:  *     <li>If a response handler accesses any shared state of the coordinator (e.g. SubscriptionState),
51:  *     it is assumed that all access to that state is synchronized on the coordinator instance by
52:  *     the caller.</li>
53:  *     <li>At most one request is pending for each node at any time. Nodes with pending requests are
54:  *     tracked and updated after processing the response. This ensures that any state (e.g. epoch)
55:  *     updated while processing responses on one thread are visible while creating the subsequent request
56:  *     on a different thread.</li>
57:  * </ul>
58:  */
59: public class Fetcher<K, V> extends AbstractFetch {
60: 
61:     private final Logger log;
