150:      * This method is called by {@link #close(Timer)} which is guarded by the {@link IdempotentCloser}) such as to only
151:      * be executed once the first time that any of the {@link #close()} methods are called. Subclasses can override
152:      * this method without the need for extra synchronization at the instance level.
153:      *
154:      * <p/>
155:      *
156:      * <em>Note</em>: this method is <code>synchronized</code> to reinstitute the 3.5 behavior:
157:      *
158:      * <blockquote>
159:      * Shared states (e.g. sessionHandlers) could be accessed by multiple threads (such as heartbeat thread), hence,
160:      * it is necessary to acquire a lock on the fetcher instance before modifying the states.
161:      * </blockquote>
162:      *
163:      * @param timer Timer to enforce time limit
164:      */
165:     // Visible for testing
166:     protected synchronized void closeInternal(Timer timer) {
167:         // we do not need to re-enable wake-ups since we are closing already
168:         client.disableWakeups();
169:         maybeCloseFetchSessions(timer);
170:         super.closeInternal(timer);
171:     }
